Perhaps the cap should be independent of the queryResultWindowSize... perhaps something like&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;queryResultMaxDocsCached&amp;gt;250&amp;lt;queryResultMaxDocsCached&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
that will allow the first number of pages to be cached?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12511048" author="koji" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2007 08:33:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with you. It should be independent of WINDOW size. The new tag will be fine for me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
